The paper discusses using reinforcement learning to improve the movement policy of a real robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of importance-weighted PGPE, a machine learning algorithm, also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The fact that the robot is learning to perform specific movements, such as target reaching and cart-pole swing up, suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of RL to control a real system suggests that the paper could also be categorized under control systems (cs.SY).
